title.narrative: Scaling up RMNCH+A - Vriddhi - IPE GLOBAL

description.narrative: (India): The USAID-supported RMNCH+A Alliance support to the GOI and state governments is to scale up key high-impact interventions of the RMNCH+A program and thereby help states accelerate progress towards ending preventable maternal and child mortality and morbidity in India,. Vriddhi has a national as well as aand state level mandate that will affect India's journey to self-reliance by strengthening its child health. At the national level, National Technical Support Unit (NTSU) and the National RMNCH+A Unit (NRU) provide assistance to GOI for the policy and guidelines development and monitoring of the RMNCH+A program implementation across the country. In the six project focus states- Delhi, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jharkhand, Punjab and Uttarakhad and High-Priority Districts therein, the support is provided through State RMNCH+A Units (SRUs) and District Technical Officers.. ..With FY 2018 funds, the project will focus on strengthening health systems in the six USAID/India focus states through establishment of think tanks which will provide technical assistance for identification, demonstration, and scaling up of promising, high-impact MCH, and FP best practices in six USAID focus states. In collaboration with state leadership, think tanks are identified These state level think tanks identified through a rigorous will facilitate the adoption and scaling up of best practices within the public health system by unlocking available GOI resources. Vriddhi will partner with GOI and states and provide technical expertise for strengthening of first referral units and for quality improvement and quality accreditation of public health facilities targeted at improving quality of care during antenatal, intrapartum and postpartum period. The project will provide techno-managerial support to GOI in strengthening supply chain management of FP commodities through the design, development, and implementation of an electronic logistics management information system. .. .
